about.summary: Converts coefficients, standard errors, significance stars, and goodness-of-fit statistics of statistical models into LaTeX tables or HTML tables/MS Word documents or to nicely formatted screen output for the R console for easy model comparison. A list of several models can be combined in a single table. The output is highly customizable. New model types can be easily implemented. (If the Zelig package, which this package enhances, cannot be found on CRAN, you can find it at <https://github.com/IQSS/Zelig>.)

Converts coefficients, standard errors, significance stars, and goodness-of-fit statistics of statistical models into LaTeX tables or HTML tables/MS Word documents or to nicely formatted screen output for the R console for easy model comparison. A list of several models can be combined in a single table. The output is highly customizable. New model types can be easily implemented. name: r-texreg
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.39.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-texreg
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/texreg_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/texreg/texreg_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 341a779f51d49c84944f32cea82eb2bbd19ef8fa9d209e9bdfc4c6f65cb76d4d

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-httr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-httr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('texreg')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('texreg')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://github.com/leifeld/texreg/
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: Converts coefficients, standard errors, significance stars, and goodness-of-fit statistics of statistical models into LaTeX tables or HTML tables/MS Word documents or to nicely formatted screen output for the R console for easy model comparison. A list of several models can be combined in a single table. The output
    is highly customizable. New model types can be easily implemented. (If the Zelig package, which this package enhances, cannot be found on CRAN, you can find it at <https://github.com/IQSS/Zelig>.)
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - izahn
    - conda-forge/r
